2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shared-workspace%20giant%20said%20it%20can%20only%20stay%20in%20business%20if%20it%20improves%20its%20liquidity%20and%20profitability%20over%20the%20next%2012%20months.%20Its%20bosses%20plans%20to%20lower%20its%20rent%20and%20tenancy%20costs%20by%20restructuring%20and%20negotiating%20better%20lease%20terms%2C%20and%20boost%20its%20revenue%20by%20attracting%20and%20retaining%20members.%20They%20also%20intend%20to%20control%20its%20costs%20and%20raise%20fresh%20capital%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20have%20balked%20at%20the%20situation.%20WeWork's%20stock%20price%20is%20down%2095%25%20in%20the%20past%20year%20alone%2C%20and%20fell%20sharply%20in%20premarket%20trading%20on%20Wednesday.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20company's%20market%20capitalization%20has%20dropped%20below%20%24500%20million%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20%2440%20billion%20valuation%20it%20once%20commanded%20as%20a%20private%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20is%20WeWork%20in%20trouble%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWeWork's%20interim%20CEO%2C%20David%20Tolley%2C%20shone%20a%20light%20on%20WeWork's%20challenges%20in%20the%20earnings%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExcess%20supply%20in%20commercial%20real%20estate%2C%20increasing%20competition%20in%20flexible%20space%20and%20macroeconomic%20volatility%20drove%20higher%20member%20churn%20and%20softer%20demand%20than%20we%20anticipated%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20slight%20decline%20in%20memberships%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20there%20were%20too%20many%20available%20commercial%20spaces%20relative%20to%20demand%20last%20quarter.%20WeWork's%20rivals%20also%20fought%20hard%20to%20win%20customers%2C%20and%20economic%20headwinds%20such%20as%20steeper%20interest%20rates%20and%20recession%20fears%20meant%20more%20WeWork%20members%20quit%20and%20fewer%20people%20signed%20up%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20headwinds%20dragged%20on%20WeWork's%20financials%20last%20quarter.%20It%20reported%20a%20net%20loss%20of%20%241.1%20billion%20on%20revenues%20of%20%241.6%20billion%20last%20quarter%2C%20and%20its%20operating%20cash%20outflow%20exceeded%20%24500%20million%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20this%20year.%20It%20also%20had%20less%20than%20%24700%20million%20of%20liquidity%20at%20the%20end%20of%20June%2C%20comprising%20%24205%20million%20of%20cash%2C%20and%20%24475%20million%20of%20borrowing%20capacity.%20That%20compares%20to%20nearly%20%24900%20million%20of%20current%20lease%20obligations%2C%20and%20over%20%2413%20billion%20in%20long-term%20lease%20obligations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20does%20this%20mean%20for%20commercial%20real%20estate%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECommercial%20real%20estate%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20hardest-hit%20sectors%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20over%20the%20last%20year.%20Developers%20rely%20heavily%20on%20debt%2C%20and%20their%20loan%20payments%20have%20soared%20due%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20hiking%20interest%20rates%20from%20nearly%20zero%20to%20north%20of%205%25%20since%20last%20spring%2C%20in%20response%20to%20historic%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20higher%20rates%20and%20the%20remote-working%20boom%20have%20pushed%20down%20prices%20of%20offices%20and%20other%20commercial%20spaces%20in%20cities.%20The%20blow%20to%20asset%20values%2C%20and%20the%20failure%20of%20several%20regional%20banks%20this%20year%2C%20have%20led%20to%20smaller%20banks%20pulling%20back%20from%20lending%20to%20commercial%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upshot%20is%20the%20industry%20is%20navigating%20steeper%20debt%20costs%2C%20reduced%20access%20to%20credit%2C%20and%20big%20declines%20in%20the%20value%20of%20their%20properties%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20wider%20economic%20downturn%20or%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Felon-musk-house-prices-housing-market-commercial-real-estate-fed-2023-5%5C%22