er%20significant%20roles.%20She%20was%20fired%20earlier%20this%20year%20in%20February%20for%20missing%20deadlines%20and%20meetings%2C%20being%20absent%20and%20uncontactable%2C%20and%20failing%20to%20complete%20a%20task%20which%20caused%20the%20industry%20regulator%20to%20fine%20her%20company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Ms%20Cheiko%20claimed%20to%20the%20FWC%20that%20her%20employer%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bpremeditated%20plan%20to%20remove%20her%20from%20the%20business%20and%20that%20she%20was%20targeted%20due%20to%20her%20mental%20health%20issues%26quot%3B.%20However%2C%20FWC's%20investigation%20found%20that%20Ms%20Cheikho%20was%20fired%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bvalid%20reason%20of%20misconduct%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20consultant%20received%20a%20formal%20warning%20in%20November%202022%20about%20her%20output%20and%20was%20put%20on%20a%20performance%20improvement%20plan.%20Insurance%20Australia%20Group%20used%20keystroke%20technology%20to%20track%20her%20cyber%20activity%20for%2049%20days%20between%20October%20and%20December%2C%20and%20found%20that%20she%20had%20%26quot%3Bvery%20low%20keystroke%20activity%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fus-woman-fills-bottle-with-alcohol-to-stop-baby-from-crying-arrested-4282510%5C%22%3EUS%20Woman%20Fills%20Bottle%20With%20Alcohol%20To%20Stop%20Baby%20From%20Crying%2C%20Arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20found%20that%20Ms%20Cheikho%20started%20work%20late%20on%2047%20days%2C%20finished%20early%20on%2029%20days%20and%20did%20not%20work%20her%20rostered%20hours%20for%2044%20days.%20It%20also%20discovered%20that%20on%204%20days%2C%20she%20did%20zero%20hours%20of%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F7news.com.au%2Fbusiness%2Fworkplace-matters%2Fwoman-fired-after-work-from-home-monitoring-found-she-wasnt-typing-enough-c-11525714%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E7%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20findings%2C%20Ms%20Cheikho%20averaged%2054%20strokes%20per%20hour%20over%20the%20duration%20of%20her%20surveillance%2C%20which%20showed%20%26quot%3Bshe%20was%20not%20presenting%20for%20work%20and%20performing%20work%20as%20required%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20consultant%20denied%20that%20she%20worked%20less%20than%20her%20set%20hours%2C%20saying%20she%20sometimes%20used%20other%20devices%20to%20log%20in.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bconfused%20and%20shocked%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20data%2C%20and%20questioned%20its%20accuracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20FWC%20Deputy%20President%20Thomas%20Roberts%20ruled%20the%20evidence%20showed%20Ms%20Cheikho%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20working%20as%20she%20was%20required%20to%20do%20during%20her%20designated%20working%20hours%26quot%3B%20while%20monitored.%20%26quot%3BThe%20applicant%20was%20dismissed%20for%20a%20valid%20reason%20of%20misconduct%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Roberts%20said%2C%20as%20per%20the%20outlet.%20He%20acknowledged%20the%20unfortunate%20situation%20but%20ruled%20that%20the%20termination%20wasn't%20unjust%20or%20unreasonable.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691579880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fnvao7r48_suzie-cheikho_625x300_09_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Faustralian-woman-fired-after-company-uses-keystroke-tech-to-monitor-her-work-from-home-4283188%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Australian%20woman%2C%20who%20was%20working%20with%20an%20insurance%20company%2C%20lost%20her%20job%20after%2018%20years%20after%20her%20firm%20used%20keystroke%20technology%20to%20monitor%20her%20work-from-home%20performance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Faustralian-woman-fired-after-company-uses-keystroke-tech-to-monitor-her-work-from-home-4283188%22