20Student%20loan%20balances%20ticked%20down%20to%20%241.57%20trillion%2C%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-will-happen-when-student-loan-payments-resume-sizeable-shock-2023-6%5C%22%3Econtinued%20payment%20pause%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20that%20also%20means%20those%20debts%20aren't%20impacting%20consumers'%20every%20day%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Ff%2F102997%2Fx%2F6b4d8d5fa9%2Fcredit-card-debt-press-release.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBankrate%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20found%20that%2060%25%20of%20those%20with%20a%20credit%20card%20balance%20%E2%80%94%2054%20million%20people%20in%20total%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20indebted%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year.%20Per%20the%20New%20York%20Fed%20report%2C%208%25%20of%20credit%20card%20debt%20balances%20were%20delinquent%20for%2090%20days%20or%20more%2C%20meaning%20that%20they%20had%20gone%20unpaid%20for%20months.%20The%20percentage%20of%20credit%20card%20debt%20flowing%20into%20serious%20delinquency%20rose%20from%203.35%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202022%20to%205.08%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUsXL2%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Transition%20into%20serious%20delinquency%20for%20credit%20card%20debt%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ECourtney%20Alev%2C%20consumer%20financial%20advocate%20at%20Credit%20Karma%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20since%20the%20Fed%20started%20raising%20interest%20rates%20a%20while%20ago%2C%20the%20personal%20finance%20site%20has%20seen%20credit%20scores%20fall%20by%20an%20average%20of%2013%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20actually%20seeing%20reflected%20in%20the%20data%20that%20people%20are%20carrying%20more%20debt%2C%20their%20utilization's%20going%20up%2C%20and%20it%20is%20seeing%20an%20impact%20on%20their%20credit%2C%26quot%3B%20Alev%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20with%20rising%20interest%20rates%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20debt%20has%20not%20been%20this%20expensive%20in%20over%20two%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Alev%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%20seven%20quarters%2C%20credit%20card%20balances%20have%20grown%20year%20over%20year%20amid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthank-the-american-retail-consumer-for-the-soft-landing-2023-7%5C%22%3Estrong%20consumer%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20high%20prices.%20However%2C%20the%20average%20credit%20card%20rate%20remains%20at%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-with-the-highest-and-lowest-credit-card-debt-2023-6%5C%22%3Eall-time%20high%20of%20over%2020%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20comes%20just%20months%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-i-have-to-resume-student-loan-payments-debt-relief-2023-7%5C%22%3Estudent-loan%20payments%20are%20set%20to%20resume%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20an%20over%20three-year%20pause.%20While%20both%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20extended%20the%20pause%20on%20federal%20payments%20and%20interest%20accrual%C2%A0numerous%20times%20to%20give%20borrowers%20financial%20relief%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20bill%20to%20raise%20the%20debt%20ceiling%20that%20Biden%20signed%20into%20law%20in%20early%20June%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoes-debt-ceiling-deal-ban-student-debt-relief-payment-pause-2023-5%5C%22%3Ecodified%20the%20end%20of%20that%20pause%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20that%20Biden%20cannot%20extend%20the%20pause%20again%20this%20year%20in%20connection%20with%20COVID-19%20%E2%80%94%20and%20interest%20will%20begin%20accruing%20again%20on%20borrowers'%20balances%20in%20September%2C%20with%20their%20first%20bill%20coming%20due%20in%20October.%20While%20the%20New%20York%20Fed's%20report%20showed%20little%20change%20to%20the%20student-loan%20portfolio%20due%20to%20the%20ongoing%20pause%2C%20the%20other%20forms%20of%20consumer%20debt%20student-loan%20borrowers%20hold%20will%20likely%20complicate%20the%20return%20to%20repayment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fabout-us%2Fblog%2Foffice-of-research-blog-update-on-student-loan-borrowers-as-payment-suspension-set-to-expire%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20found%20that%20median%20payments%20on%20other%20debt%20obligations%20increased%20by%2024%25%20for%20borrowers%20likely%20returning%20to%20repayment%2C%20and%20more%20than%20one-in-thirteen%20borrowers%20are%20currently%20behind%20on%20other%20payment%20obligations.%20Still%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20announced%20a%2012-month%20%26quot%3Bon-ramp%26quot%3B%20for%20borrowers%20once%20payments%20resume%20during%20which%20missed%20payments%20will%20not%20be%20reported%20to%20credit%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20record-high%20credit%20card%20balances%2C%20there%20are%20some%20silver%20linings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20over%20half%20of%20cardholders%20avoid%20interest%20by%20paying%20in%20full%20each%20month%2C%20so%20credit%20cards%20are%20working%20for%20them%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20rewards%20and%20buyer%20protections%2C%26quot%3B%20Ted%20Rossman%2C%20senior%20industry%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate%2C%20said%20in%20a%20note%20after%20the%20New%20York%20Fed%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Rossman%20pointed%20out%2C%20%26quot%3Bconsumer%20spending%20powers%20about%2070%25%20of%20economic%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20while%20many%20Americans%20are%20going%20into%20more%20debt%20racking%20up%20credit%20card%20bills%2C%20the%20broader%20economy%20is%20benefiting.%20With%20credit%20flowing%20rather%20freely%2C%20this%20debt%20peak%20may%20not%20have%20a%20disastrous%20impact%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20generally%20good%20economy%20could%20also%20help%20Americans%20handle%20their%20debt%20burdens.%20%26quot%3BOverall%2C%20the%20strong%20job%20market%20has%20most%20consumers%20in%20a%20pretty%20good%20position%2C%20despite%20high%20inflation%20and%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Rossman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWages%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fempsit.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estill%20grew%20in%20July%2C%20for%20instance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-is-inflation-looking-consumer-price-index-june-data-2023-7%5C%22%3EInflation%20has%20been%20slowing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20new%20data%20out%20later%20this%20week.%20But%20while%20those%20are%20all%20good%20signs%20for%20the%20broader%20economy%2C%20it%20might%20not%20mean%20much%20for%20Americans%20sitting%20on%20piles%20of%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20dealing%20with%20an%20untenable%20amount%20of%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%20or%20worried%20about%20student%20loan%20payments%20restarting%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejkaplan%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ensheidlower%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40insider.