paigned%20for%20re-election%20following%20a%20term%20marked%20by%20controversy.%20During%20his%20tenure%2C%20Yameen%20had%20jailed%20all%20the%20main%20opposition%20leaders%20and%20supreme%20court%20judges%20in%20addition%20to%20antagonising%20India%20by%20harbouring%20close%20ties%20with%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20when%20Maldivian%20Democratic%20Party%E2%80%99s%20(MDP)%20Ibrahim%20Solih%2C%20the%20joint%20opposition%20candidate%2C%20won%20by%20a%20margin%20of%2016%25%20in%20the%20first%20round%20itself%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fafter-flawed-campaign-maldives-votes-in-high-numbers-in-critical-presidential-polls%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20was%20a%20big%20upset%20for%20Yameen%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20key%20factor%20for%20the%20opposition%20victory%20had%20been%20huge%20voter%20turnout%20at%2089.2%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20Yameen%20is%20behind%20bars%20and%20disqualified%20from%20contesting%20the%20elections.%20However%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20Solih%20will%20have%20smooth%20run.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20eight%20candidates%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20this%20is%20the%20largest%20pool%20of%20candidates%20ever%20taking%20part%20in%20a%20presidential%20election%20in%20Maldive%E2%80%99s%20history.%20The%20second-highest%20count%20occurred%20in%20the%202008%20presidential%20elections%2C%20where%20six%20candidates%20were%20in%20contention.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20look%20at%20the%20key%20candidates%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIbrahim%20Solih%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20paper%2C%20President%20Solih%20should%20be%20doing%20well.%20There%20has%20been%20political%20stability%20during%20his%20tenure%20and%20the%20country%20managed%20to%20recover%20relatively%20well%20after%20the%20difficult%20pandemic%20years.%20His%20administration%20also%20repaired%20frayed%20relations%20with%20India%20without%20alienating%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20his%20electoral%20calculations%20are%20not%20as%20favourable.%20Two%20parties%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20MDP-led%20ruling%20coalition%20are%20fielding%20their%20own%20candidates%20in%20the%20presidential%20elections.%20Former%20President%20Mohamed%20Nasheed%20split%20and%20formed%20his%20own%20party%20after%20he%20lost%20the%20presidential%20primary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Solih%20remains%20the%20frontrunner%2C%20there%20is%20uncertainty%20if%20he%20would%20secure%20an%20outright%20win%20in%20the%20first%20round.%20When%20the%20election%20advances%20to%20the%20second%20round%20with%20only%20two%20candidates%2C%20he%20will%20have%20to%20deploy%20his%20political%20acumen%20in%20garnering%20support%20from%20the%20remaining%20political%20parties%20to%20secure%20the%20majority%20of%20votes%20needed%20for%20victory.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20295px)%2085vw%2C%20295px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09122949%2FF2_XhqAagAAwuQ3.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22295%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09122949%2FF2_XhqAagAAwuQ3.jpeg%20951w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09122949%2FF2_XhqAagAAwuQ3-238x300.jpeg%20238w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09122949%2FF2_XhqAagAAwuQ3-812x1024.jpeg%20812w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667316%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22372%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMohamed%20Muizzu.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40bkhussainmanik%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMohamed%20Muizzu%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20Yameen%20failed%20to%20get%20relief%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20being%20blocked%20from%20standing%20in%20the%20presidential%20elections%2C%20he%20reluctantly%20endorsed%20the%20presidential%20candidate%20of%20his%20alliance%20partner%2C%20People%E2%80%99s%20National%20Congress%20(PNC).%20A%20civil%20engineer%20with%20a%20doctorate%20from%20University%20of%20Leeds%2C%20Muizzu%20had%20been%20the%20housing%20minister%20under%20the%20Yameen%20government%2C%20which%20is%20an%20important%20political%20portfolio%20due%20to%20the%20high%20demand%20for%20affordable%20housing%20in%20the%20limited%20urban%20areas%20in%20the%20archipelago%20nation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20he%20was%20elected%20as%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F66743%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20non-MDP%20mayor%20of%20the%20capital%20city%20of%20Male%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20hosts%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20population.%20While%20Yameen%20had%20been%20behind%20bars%2C%20Muizzu%20had%20kept%20up%20contacts%20with%20China%20through%20outreach%20events.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Maldivian%20media%2C%20he%20said%20at%20an%20online%20webinar%20in%20September%202022%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F77787%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erelations%20between%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives%20(PPM)%20and%20Communist%20Party%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20were%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfoundation%20of%20diplomatic%20relations%20between%20Maldives%20and%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20he%20is%20known%20to%20be%20close%20to%20Yameen%2C%20his%20role%20as%20mayor%20had%20meant%20a%20high-visibility%20political%20profile%20that%20seems%20to%20have%20fuelled%20his%20presidential%20ambitions.%20Muizzu%20officially%20left%20his%20party%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.mv%2Fnews%2F28642%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ejoined%20the%20PNC%20only%20last%20week%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20after%20the%20latter%20announced%20that%20they%20will%20submit%20a%20presidential%20nomination%20as%20a%20contingency%20plan%20if%20Yameen%20was%20not%20able%20to%20clear%20the%20legal%20hurdles%20to%20stand%20for%20elections.%20He%20was%20then%20filed%20his%20nomination%20as%20the%20PNC%E2%80%99s%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20with%20Yameen%20eventually%20coming%20around%20to%20give%20his%20official%20endorsement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQasim%20Ibrahim%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20businessman%20in%20Maldives%2C%20Qasim%20Ibrahim%20of%20Jumhooree%20Party%20(JP)%20has%20always%20been%20seen%20to%20be%20a%20kingmaker%20due%20to%20his%20ability%20to%20swing%20elections%20in%20the%20second%20round.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20will%20be%20contesting%20elections%20for%20the%20third%20time%2C%20after%20standing%20in%20the%202008%20and%202013%20polls.%20Ibrahim%20may%20not%20have%20the%20numbers%20to%20win%20the%20elections%20outright%2C%20but%20he%20has%20a%20captive%20vote%20bank%20that%20is%20wooed%20by%20all%20parties.%20As%20the%20owner%20of%20several%20resorts%2C%20analysts%20believe%20that%20Qasim%20can%20%E2%80%98transfer%E2%80%99%20votes%20from%20his%20extensive%20workforce%2C%20which%20could%20be%20enough%20to%20swing%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20multi-party%20presidential%20elections%20in%202008%2C%20he%20won%2015%25%20of%20the%20votes%20in%20the%20first%20round%20and%20was%20eliminated.%20Thereafter%2C%20he%20announced%20support%20for%20MDP%E2%80%99s%20Mohamed%20Nasheed%2C%20who%20eventually%20defeated%20long-term%20dictator%20Maumoon%20Gayoom%20in%20the%20second%20round.%20While%20he%20joined%20Nasheed%E2%80%99s%20cabinet%2C%20Qasim%20soon%20left%20after%20a%20fall-out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%202013%20elections%2C%20he%20got%2024%25%20of%20votes%20in%20the%20first%20round.%20A%20sizeable%20amount%20of%20his%20support%20shifted%20Abdulla%20Yameen%2C%20who%20secured%20victory%20over%20Nasheed%20by%20amassing%2051%25%20of%20the%20votes%20during%20the%20second%20round.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQasim%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20stand%20for%20elections%20in%202018%20due%20to%20a%20conviction%2C%20but%20supported%20Solih%20as%20joint%20opposition%20candidate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20declining%20Solih%E2%80%99s%20invitation%20to%20join%20the%20re-election%20campaign%2C%20Qasim%E2%80%99s%20next%20move%20will%20be%20closely%20watched%20to%20ascertain%20which%20side%20he%20aligns%20with%2C%20should%20a%20second%20round%20of%20voting%20take%20place.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20other%20players%20behind%20the%20scenes%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20316px)%2085vw%2C%20316px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09123326%2FAbdulla_Yameen_Abdul_Gayoom_in_January_2014-223x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22316%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09123326%2FAbdulla_Yameen_Abdul_Gayoom_in_January_2014-223x300.jpg%20223w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09123326%2FAbdulla_Yameen_Abdul_Gayoom_in_January_2014.jpg%20400w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667320%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22425%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAbdulla%20Yameen.%20Photo%3A%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20(GODL-India).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAbdulla%20Yameen%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20former%20president%2C%20the%202023%20elections%20will%20be%20a%20test%20of%20his%20political%20relevancy.%20After%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20rejected%20his%20appeal%20for%20overturning%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20(EC)%20rejection%20of%20his%20candidature%20due%20to%20conviction%2C%20Yameen%20had%20called%20on%20his%20own%20party%20and%20alliance%20partner%20to%20boycott%20the%20elections.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20PPM-PNC%E2%80%99s%20top%20decision%20body%20rejected%20the%20boycott%20proposals%2C%20Yameen%20still%20did%20not%20accept%20it.%20If%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20stand%20for%20elections%2C%20Yameen%20would%20have%20preferred%20another%20face%20from%20his%20own%20party%2C%20with%20names%20of%20former%20president%20Ahmed%20Waheed%20and%20his%20nephew%20Gasim%20Maumoon%20floating%20around.%20However%2C%20Yameen%20was%20obviously%20reluctant%20to%20push%20for%20Muizzu%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20despite%20the%20latter%20having%20expressed%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20his%20own%20proxy%20candidate%20would%20prevent%20Yameen%20from%20going%20into%20political%20obscurity.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Yameen%20would%20have%20preferred%20a%20surrogate%20candidate%20who%20was%20more%20politically%20dependent%20on%20him%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20consideration%20stems%20from%20the%20recognition%20that%20even%20a%20purported%20proxy%20could%20readily%20break%20free%20from%20control%2C%20similar%20to%20how%20Yameen%20consolidated%20power%20and%20distanced%20himself%20from%20his%20elder%20brother%20Maumoon%20Gayoom%20after%20the%202013%20elections.%20The%20mayor%20of%20Male%2C%20despite%20his%20public%20loyalty%20to%20Yameen%20and%20the%20party%2C%20had%20his%20own%20political%20base.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMohamed%20Nasheed%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERight%20after%20the%202018%20elections%2C%20there%20had%20been%20rumblings%20that%20Nasheed%20and%20Solih%2C%20childhood%20friends%20with%20familial%20links%2C%20would%20eventually%20clash%20due%20to%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20on%20assuming%20a%20more%20prominent%20role.%20With%20Solih%20reluctant%20to%20support%20Nasheed%E2%80%99s%20demand%20of%20changing%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20system%2C%20the%20foundation%20for%20their%20estrangement%20was%20laid.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20Nasheed%E2%80%99s%20faction%20broke%20off%20from%20the%20MDP%2C%20he%20had%20been%20holding%20talks%20with%20other%20parties%20to%20agree%20on%20a%20common%20presidential%20candidate.%20But%20the%20talks%20broke%20down%2C%20with%20the%20main%20hurdle%20apparently%20being%20PPM%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20on%20Abdulla%20Yameen%20being%20their%20only%20presidential%20candidate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Democrats%20have%20fielded%20their%20own%20candidate%2C%20he%20is%20also%20continuing%20to%20hold%20talks%20on%20a%20common%20strategy%20for%20the%20second%20round.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMaumoon%20Gayoom%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20after%20Nasheed%20ended%20his%2030-year-old%20rule%20in%20the%202008%20elections%2C%20Gayoom%20continued%20to%20be%20a%20dominant%20political%20actor%20in%20the%20Maldivian%20elections.%20Gayoom%20was%20presumed%20to%20be%20the%20real%20power%20when%20his%20half-brother%2C%20Yameen%20won%20the%202013%20elections%2C%20but%20both%20of%20them%20soon%20found%20themselves%20on%20different%20sides.%20Gayoom%2C%20along%20with%20his%20son%2C%20Faris%20Maumoon%20were%20even%20jailed%20by%20the%20Yameen%20administration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20a%20new%20political%20faction%2C%20Gayoom%20joined%20the%20opposition%2C%20which%20included%20Nasheed%2C%20in%20supporting%20Solih.%20While%20his%20newly%20formed%20party%20Maldives%20Reform%20Movement%20(MRM)%20does%20not%20have%20the%20same%20clout%2C%20Gayoom%20has%20remained%20active%20behind%20the%20scenes.%20All%20of%20his%20four%20children%20are%20affiliated%20to%20different%20political%20parties%2C%20including%20Yameen%E2%80%99s%20PPM.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20being%20a%20member%20of%20the%20ruling%20coalition%2C%20Gayoom%E2%80%99s%20MRM%20had%20also%20decided%20to%20jump%20into%20the%20presidential%20elections.%20The%20EC%20had%20earlier%20dissolved%20MRM%20after%20the%20party%20failed%20to%20meet%20the%20legal%20requirement%20of%203000%20members.%20MRM%20went%20to%20the%20civil%20court%2C%20which%20ruled%20against%20the%20EC%E2%80%99s%20move.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.mv%2Fpresidential_election_2023%2F28705%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFaris%20announced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20he%20would%20stand%20as%20an%20independent%20candidate%20and%20submitted%20his%20nomination%20just%20before%20the%20deadline.%20With%20at%20least%20one%20member%20of%20his%20family%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20Gayoom%20has%20ensured%20that%20he%20remains%20part%20of%20the%20political%20calculations%20after%20September%209.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691568008000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09122311%2FF1OKCIcaIAI3sDv.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaldives-explainer-presidential-election-ibrahim-solih%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20Solih%20remains%20the%20frontrunner%2C%20there%20is%20uncertainty%20if%20he%20would%20secure%20an%20outright%20win%20in%20the%20first%20round.%20With%20eight%20candidates%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20this%20is%20the%20largest%20pool%20ever%20taking%20part%20in%20a%20presidential%20election%20in%20Maldive's%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaldives-explainer-presidential-election-ibrahim-solih%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Smriti%20Irani%20slams%20Congress%20over%20Rahul's%20'murder%20of%20India'%20remark%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691567186000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fthumb%2Fmsid-102566178%2Cwidth-1070